      {
        "id": 4312424,
        "name": "Alan Rath",
        "username": "Alan_Rath",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/alan_rath/{size}/644_2.png",
        "created_at": "2024-03-05T04:04:19.274Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Everyone\u2019s tastes are different lol.  I\u2019ve found most 21 reds from both Burgundy and Beaujolais to be one the leaner side, sometimes too austere for me. But I\u2019m not fond of solar vintages, like 15 and 18. 19 is at the limit for me, and a lot of 20s have been too ripe. Guess I have a pretty narrow range lol. Have loved most 16s and 14s.</p>",
